The paper discusses a method for discovering causal structure from non-experimental data, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method relies on independent component analysis (ICA), which is a statistical technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.ST).
